description:
Extraordinary Museums of Southeast Asia
Harry N. Abrams | 2001 | ISBN: 0810929945 | English | 226 pages | PDF | 52.3 MB

An illustrated guide, in one handy paperback volume, to thirty of Southeast Asia's most interesting and unusual museums. Reflecting the rich diversity of the cultural heritage of the area, this guide encompasses art, history, ethnographic, and military collections, ranging from the national museums of Cambodia and Malaysia to relatively unknown treasures such as the Tribal Museum in Chiang Mai, Thailand
